        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 6. Porcupinella spp. A world map of distribution. Porcupinella profunda (red circle), Porcupinella tasmanica sp. nov. (red triangle) B detailed map of the type locality of Porcupinella tasmanica sp. nov. (yellow circle = type locality). Map data 2020 Google." , "Figure 5. Porcupinella profunda. Non-type material A-B CASIZ 180424 C-D CASIZ 180425 E-F CASIZ 180426; Scale bar: 20 mm." , "Figure 4. Porcupinella profunda. Diagram of external Colonial morphology (CASIZ 180424). Abbreviations: a - axis; dt - distal terminus of the colony; k - keel of the stalk; la - lateral autozooid; p - peduncle, r - rachis; s - siphonozooid ta - terminal autozooid; tb - terminal bulb of the peduncle. Scale bar: 10 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/512428" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/512427" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/512426" .

